  ### Additional context and logs
  
  Starting with [release 1.5.26](https://github.com/qos-ch/logback/releases/tag/v_1.5.26), Logback has introduced new version properties files that are read at initialization time. When using a native image these files aren't available as resources, causing warnings during startup:
  ```
  |-WARN in ch.qos.logback.classic.LoggerContext[default] - Versions of logback-classic and ? are different or unknown.
  ```
  This is especially annoying because a single warning during Logback initialization will cause *all* of its internal startup logging to become visible, so this produces a lot of noise.
  
  For logback-classic, the file that needs to be available as a resource is `ch/qos/logback/classic/logback-classic-version.properties`. For logback-core, it's `ch/qos/logback/core/logback-core-version.properties`. 
  
